# Hebrew & RTL Guidelines

## HTML Base Configuration
```html
<html lang="he" dir="rtl">
```

## RTL-Safe Tailwind Classes

### Use Logical Properties (DO ✅)
```tsx
// Positioning
className="start-0"      // instead of left-0
className="end-0"        // instead of right-0
className="-end-1"       // instead of -right-1

// Margins
className="ms-4"         // margin-start (right in RTL)
className="me-4"         // margin-end (left in RTL)

// Padding
className="ps-4"         // padding-start
className="pe-4"         // padding-end

// Text alignment
className="text-right"   // default for Hebrew
className="text-start"   // logical start

// Animations
className="slide-in-from-start"  // slides from right in RTL
```

### Avoid Physical Properties (DON'T ❌)
```tsx
// These break in RTL:
className="left-0"       // Use start-0
className="right-0"      // Use end-0
className="ml-4"         // Use ms-4
className="mr-4"         // Use me-4
className="pl-4"         // Use ps-4
className="pr-4"         // Use pe-4
```

